# AetherLabs Project Rules

## Package Manager
- Always use `pnpm` instead of `npm` for all package management commands
- Use `pnpm add <package>` for dependencies
- Use `pnpm add -D <package>` for dev dependencies
- Use `pnpm install` for installing dependencies
- Use `pnpm run <script>` for running scripts

## Code Style & Standards
- Use TypeScript for all new files (.ts, .tsx)
- Use functional components with React hooks
- Always include React import: `import React from 'react'`
- Use 'use client' directive for client components in Next.js App Router
- Follow Next.js 14+ App Router conventions
- Use strict TypeScript mode (strict: true)
- Use ES2017 target for TypeScript compilation

## Project Structure
- Components should be in `src/` directory
- UI components in `components/ui/` (shadcn/ui)
- Pages in `app/` directory following Next.js App Router structure
- Use absolute imports with `@/` alias (configured in tsconfig.json)
- Landing page components in `src/LandingPage/`
- Services in `src/services/`
- Utilities in `lib/` directory
- Content files (MDX) in `content/` directory

## Imports & Paths
- Use absolute imports with `@/` alias: `@/components/ui/button`
- Import React explicitly: `import React from 'react'`
- Use named exports for components
- Use default exports for page components

## UI Components
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`
- Use Radix UI primitives (already installed)
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Use lucide-react for icons
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for className merging

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use CSS variables for theming (defined in globals.css)
- Follow shadcn/ui "new-york" style
- Use Tailwind config from `tailwind.config.ts`

## Next.js Conventions
- Use App Router (app/ directory)
- Use server components by default
- Mark client components with 'use client'
- Use `useRouter` from `next/navigation` for navigation
- Use metadata exports for SEO

## Form Handling
- Use React hooks for form state management
- Validate forms before submission
- Use toast notifications from `@/hooks/use-toast` for feedback
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages

## Backend Integration
- Supabase for backend services
- Use `@/src/lib/supabase` for Supabase client
- AWS Amplify for some backend features
- API routes in `app/api/` directory

## Content Management
- Use MDX for content files (terms, privacy, etc.)
- Use `gray-matter` for parsing frontmatter
- Content files in `content/` directory
- Use `getMDXContent()` from `lib/mdx.ts` for loading MDX

## Git & Version Control
- Follow existing .gitignore patterns
- Commit messages should be descriptive

## Testing & Quality
- Run `pnpm run lint` before committing
- Fix linting errors before proceeding
- Use TypeScript strict mode for type safety

## Project Context
- This is AetherLabs - an art authentication platform using blockchain and NFC technology
- Tech Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript, React 18, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Supabase, Radix UI
- Target: Art galleries, artists, and collectors for artwork authentication

